<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7161> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7161" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 43. He was proscribed in 43 but was saved by his wife and his freedman, T. Vinius Philopoemen, being hidden in a chest in the latter's house (Suet. Aug. 27.2; App. BC 4.44; Dio 47.7.4-5). Augustus rewarded him with equestrian rank. Vinius was probably of senatorial rank, and may have attained the praetorship. According to Tacitus (Hist. 1.48), the father of T. Vinius Rufinus (PIR 3.437, no. 450; De Laet 170, no. 1157), born A.D. 21/22, belonged to a praetorian family, and his grandfather also, but Tacitus (Hist. 1.48) writes that his maternus avus was one of the proscribed. (TJC) See Syme, Sallust 228, note 52; Wiseman, NM 275, no. 496.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10516> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10516" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/27> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Hinard makes him praetorius when proscribed" .
